Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5. Defendant advised if released from custody it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping, a warrant issued or high cash bail.

Defendant Nakiaya J Smith-Jones appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Christopher John Ertl appeared by video for Nakiaya J Smith-Jones. Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant pled not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.
